			<p class="first_paragraph">
				Lastly, the way that Clarise’s character is used as a framing device for the storyline also contributes to her character development. It’s no coincidence that the storyline takes place with Clarise on the cusp of graduating from the academy and that the narrative thrust of the Lecter plot directly parallels Clarise’s transition from student to professional. The story isn’t just about solving the Buffalo Bill kidnapping, it’s also about watching Clarise develop from an intelligent student lacking confidence in herself into a fully-formed, self-aware professional.	
			</p>
