				Once you’ve finished that, watch the film. As you watch think about the following questions: 
				How does Cosmo present himself to the rest of the world? What do you think of him? What does he want you to think of him?
				Try to work out the cause-and-effect chain. What events trigger the chain? How tightly linked is the chain?
				How is Cassavetes’ discourse unusual?
			</p>
